Class: <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00016>

    Annotations: 
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "A layer is a spatially extended, contiguous part of an object, which can be clearly distinguished from other parts of the object lying above or below it by its physical properties."@en,
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "Eine Schicht ist ein flächenmäßig ausgedehntes, zusammenhängender Teil eines Objektes bildet, welche durch ihre physikalischen Eigenschaften von darüber oder darunterliegenden anderen Teilen des Objektes klar unterschieden werden kann."@de,
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000600> "Please note that layers in this sense are bona fide parts of objects in the sense of BFO. I.e., there is a physical distinction between the layer and the rest of the object. (E.g., a coat of paint is a layer of the product.) This distinguishes this kind of layers from surface layers as fiat object parts.",
        rdfs:label "Schicht"@de,
        rdfs:label "layer"@en
    
    SubClassOf: 
