Class: <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00109>

    Annotations: 
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "A process attribute inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's magnitude of the temporal extent between the starting and ending points in the case of a temporally continuous process. In the case of a non-continuous process, the process duration is the sum of the durations of the discrete parts of the process."@en,
        rdfs:label "process duration"@en,
        rdfs:seeAlso "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001309"^^xsd:anyURI
    
    SubClassOf: 
        <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000008>
    
    
Class: <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00110>

    Annotations: 
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "Deposition time is a process duration of an application of substance (e.g., a vacuum deposition process), which expresses the duration during which material is deposited on a substrate.",
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000600> "This does not include parts of the manifacturing process, during which no deposition happens. E.g., if the substrate needs to be heated before the deposition process starts or the process is interrupted (e.g., using a shutter or because there is no plasma), these time intervals do not contribute  to the deposition duration.",
        rdfs:label "Beschichtungszeit"@de,
        rdfs:label "deposition duration"@en
    
    SubClassOf: 
        <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00109>
         and (<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025006> some <https://w3id.org/coato/coat_00016>)
    
    
Class: <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00111>

