Class: <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00129>

    Annotations: 
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "A plasma is a material that is in the plasma state."@en,
        rdfs:label "plasma"@en,
        <https://w3id.org/coato/coat_00001> "Revisit this issue with the PMD Core folks. Their ontology has aggregate state values, but only as value specifications, but not as qualities.

The distinction between chemical substance and material in PMDCore is not clear to me. Hence, I am not sure whether gas should be defined as a kind of chemical substance of material."
    
    EquivalentTo: 
        <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000000>
         and (<https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00130> some <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00107>)
         and (<https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00130> only <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00107>)
    
    SubClassOf: 
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000086> some <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00134>,
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000086> some <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00140>
    
    
Class: <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00131>

    Annotations: 
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "A gas is a material that is in the gas state."@en,
        rdfs:label "gas"@en,
        <https://w3id.org/coato/coat_00001> "Revisit this issue with the PMD Core folks. Their ontology has aggregate state values, but only as value specifications, but not as qualities."
    
    EquivalentTo: 
        <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000000>
         and (<https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00130> some <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00077>)
         and (<https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00130> only <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00077>)
    
    
Class: <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00132>

    Annotations: 
        rdfs:label "chemical substance quality"@en,
        rdfs:seeAlso "http://purl.allotrope.org/ontologies/quality#AFQ_0000250"@en
    
    SubClassOf: 
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000019>
    
    
Class: <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00134>

    Annotations: 
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "The electron density is the number of electron per volume unit."@en,
        rdfs:label "electron density"@en
    
    SubClassOf: 
        <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00136>
    
    
Class: <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00135>

    Annotations: 
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "The number density is an intensive quantity used to describe the degree of concentration of countable objects (particles, molecules, phonons, cells, galaxies, etc.) in physical space: three-dimensional volumetric number density, two-dimensional areal number density, or one-dimensional linear number density."@en,
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> "wikipedia"@en,
        rdfs:label "number density"@en,
        rdfs:seeAlso "http://purl.allotrope.org/ontologies/quality#AFQ_0000180"@en
    
    SubClassOf: 
        <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000597>
    
    
Class: <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00136>

    Annotations: 
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "The  volumetric number density is an intensive quantity used to describe the degree of concentration of countable objects (particles, molecules, phonons, cells, galaxies, etc.) in a three-dimensional space."@en,
        rdfs:label "volumetric number density"@en,
        <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "particle density"@en
    
    SubClassOf: 
        <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00135>
    
    
Class: <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00137>

    Annotations: 
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "The  area number density is an intensive quantity used to describe the degree of concentration of countable objects (particles, molecules, phonons, cells, galaxies, etc.) in a two-dimensional space."@en,
        rdfs:label "areal number density"@en
    
    SubClassOf: 
        <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00135>
    
    
Class: <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00138>

    Annotations: 
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "The  linear number density is an intensive quantity used to describe the degree of concentration of countable objects (particles, molecules, phonons, cells, galaxies, etc.) in a one dimensional space."@en,
        rdfs:label "linear number density"@en
    
    SubClassOf: 
        <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00135>
    
    
Class: <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00139>

    Annotations: 
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "A quality that is the extent of space between two entities"@en,
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> "http://purl.allotrope.org/ontologies/quality#AFQ_0000032"@en,
        rdfs:label "distance"@en,
        rdfs:seeAlso "http://purl.allotrope.org/ontologies/quality#AFQ_0000032"@en
    
    SubClassOf: 
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000145>
    
    
Class: <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00140>

    Annotations: 
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "Mean free path is the average distance over which a moving particle (such as an atom, a molecule, or a photon) travels before substantially changing its direction or energy (or, in a specific context, other properties), typically as a result of one or more successive collisions with other particles."@en,
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mean_free_path"@en,
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000600> "The quality inheres in a portion of matter that is the aggregate of the moving particles."@en,
        rdfs:label "mean free path"@en
    
    SubClassOf: 
        <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00089>
    
    
Class: <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00142>

    Annotations: 
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "In chemistry, a formal charge in the covalent view of chemical bonding, is the hypothetical charge assigned to an atom in a molecule, assuming that electrons in all chemical bonds are shared equally between atoms, regardless of relative electronegativity."@en,
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Formal_charge"@en,
        rdfs:label "formal charge"@en
    
    SubClassOf: 
        <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00132>
    
    
Class: <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00146>

    Annotations: 
        rdfs:label "DEPRECATED aluminium"@en,
        rdfs:seeAlso <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0020071>,
        owl:deprecated true
    
    
Class: <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00148>

    Annotations: 
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112> "The (portion of) copper that is part of a given bronze statue.",
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000112> "The (portion of) nitrogen that is part of the (portion of) air contained in the oval office."@en,
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "A mixture component is a (portion of) pure substance that is a part of mixture.",
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116> "The axiom should really say: 
''pure substance'  and ('part of' exactly 1 mixture)'
However, according to Hermit part_of is not a simple property (probably because it is used as part of a role composition), and, thus, the restrictions of OWL prevent its use in cardinality restrictions.",
        rdfs:label "mixture component"@en
    
    EquivalentTo: 
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_60003>
         and (<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050> some <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00117>)
    
    
Class: <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00150>

    Annotations: 
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "In a mixture of gases, each constituent gas has a partial pressure which is the notional pressure of that constituent gas as if it alone occupied the entire volume of the original mixture at the same temperature."@en,
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Partial_pressure"@en,
        rdfs:label "partial pressure"@en
    
    SubClassOf: 
