Class: <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00160>

    Annotations: 
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "Arcing is an unwanted discharge of electrical potential applied to the sputtering target surface shorting over to ground potential through the plasma during the deposition process causing a short circuit."@en,
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000119> "https://plasmaterials.com/arching-problems-in-the-plasma/"@en,
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000600> "This high energy displacement can cause severe damage to the equipment being employed (power supply, cathode assembly, magnetic enhancement, substrate, etc.) and more than likely will cause damage to the target itself, depending on the amount energy being dissipated."@en,
        rdfs:label "arcing"@en
    
    SubClassOf: 
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000015>,
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050> some <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00000>,
