Class: <https://w3id.org/coato/coat_00000>

    Annotations: 
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "Pulse behaviour is a process characteristic that describes the temporal pattern of variation of electrical power or voltage applied during a pulsed directe current sputtering process, including the timing, duration, frequency, amplitude, and waveform of pulses delivered to the plasma."@en,
        rdfs:label "pulse behaviour"@en
    
    SubClassOf: 
        <https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0000008>
         and (<https://w3id.org/pmd/co/PMD_0025006> some <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00001>)
    
    
Class: <https://w3id.org/coato/coat_00002>

    Annotations: 
        <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "A magnetron is a sputter system that is designed to generate and sustain a plasma by means of a magnetic field arranged near the target surface, such that charged particles, particularly electrons, are confined and guided to increase ionization efficiency and thereby enhance the sputtering of target material and its subsequent deposition onto a substrate."@en,
        rdfs:label "magnetron"@en
    
    EquivalentTo: 
        <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00031>
         and (<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000051> some <https://w3id.org/coato/#coat_00030>)
    
    
